File: The infected soldiers will remain quarantined until they recover. JOHANNESBURG - About 40 South African National Defence Force members have been infected with COVID-19. The battalion was deployed from Cape Town to Limpopo, to patrol the border with Zimbabwe. The soldiers were quarantined both before leaving Cape Town and on arrival in Limpopo. READ: COVID-19: SANDF medical teams to be deployed to ECape Despite this, several members showed symptoms and the entire battalion was tested. The infected soldiers will remain quarantined until they recover. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.